        <updateDate>2010-11-09T15:46:34Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Community Awareness Act of 2010 - Amends the Cranston-Gonzalez National Affordable Housing Act, with respect to supportive housing for persons with disabilities, to prohibit the Secretary of Housing and Urban Affairs (HUD) from providing assistance to an applicant for such supportive housing unless the applicant has held at least one local public open community meeting regarding the application that meets specified requirements.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Community Awareness Act of 2010</title>
    <titles>
